steps: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F.. Line a 13x9x2-inch baking dish with Reynolds Wrap® Pan Lining Paper with parchment paper side facing up toward food. Crimp Pan Lining Paper around rim of dish set aside.. Whisk together cream cheese, mayonnaise, milk and garlic powder in a large bowl. Stir in artichokes, spinach, the cheeses and roasted red pepper until combined. Spread in lined pan in an even layer.. Bake uncovered 25 to 30 minutes or until edges are bubbling and starting to brown. Serve with crackers or chips.

name: Alaskan Spicy Spinach Dip
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'pepperjack cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'half-and-half cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'tomato, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, diced'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced red bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'spinach, rinsed and chopped'}
steps: Over a double boiler slowly melt the pepperjack cheese. When the cheese is melted whisk in half and half until smooth and creamy. Stir in tomato, onion, red bell pepper and chopped spinach. Transfer to a serving bowl. Serve warm with tortilla chips or bread.

name: Refreshing Cucumber Salsa
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'bunch', 'name': 'fresh spinach, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cucumber, cubed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'tomato, cubed'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'red onion, cut into 1/4-inch pieces'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'lemon, juiced'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sea salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}
steps: Mix spinach, cucumber, tomato, red onion, garlic, lemon juice, olive oil, salt, and black pepper in a large bowl. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate, 1 hour to overnight.

name: Chicken Florentine Dip
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(10.5 ounce) cans', 'name': 'condensed, 98% fat-free cream of chicken soup with 30% less sodium'}, {'quantity': '9', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'diced cooked chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) container', 'name': 'reduced-fat sour cream'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded part-skim mozzarella cheese'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'skim milk, or more as needed'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) package', 'name': 'frozen chopped spinach - thawed, drained, and squeezed dry'}
steps: Combine condensed soup, chicken, sour cream mozzarella cheese, 1/2 cup skim milk, and Parmesan cheese in a slow cooker. Add spinach, pulling it apart and shredding it as you put it in. Mix until well blended.. Cover and cook on Low until all cheeses are melted and the dip is deliciously gooey, 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Add up to 1/2 cup more milk if you feel the dip is cooking up too thick.

name: Vegan Spinach Dip with Artichokes
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) tub', 'name': 'almond cream cheese alternative spread'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'coconut yogurt'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'frozen chopped spinach, thawed and drained'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegan shredded Parmesan-style cheese'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) can', 'name': 'artichoke hearts, drained and chopped'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded vegan mozzarella-style cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Combine vegan cream cheese and coconut yogurt in a bowl and stir to combine. Mix in spinach, vegan Parmesan, garlic, and Italian seasoning. Fold in artichoke hearts and season with salt and pepper.. Grease the bottom and sides of an 8x8-inch oven-safe baking dish with olive oil. Pour in spinach mixture and spread out evenly. Top with vegan mozzarella.. Bake in the preheated oven until cheese is beginning to brown, about 25 minutes. Remove from oven and serve warm.

name: Spinach and Gorgonzola Cheese Ball
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(8 ounce) packages', 'name': 'cream cheese, softened'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) package', 'name': 'frozen chopped spinach, thawed and drained'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'crumbled Gorgonzola cheese'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'slivered almonds'}
steps: Stir together cream cheese and spinach in a large bowl; mix well. Gently fold in Gorgonzola crumbles. Shape cheese mixture into a ball. Roll cheese ball in slivered almonds. Wrap well; chill until firm, about 1 hour.
